# Backstop against ever committing private material to this public repo.
#
# publish-to-github-repo.command only copies the github/ folder, so the private files below
# normally cannot reach here at all. This file is the second line of defence
# for the case where someone runs `git add` by hand in the clone.

# The editor holds the ECDSA PRIVATE SIGNING KEY. Never in this repo.
editor.html
manifest-editor.json

# Plaintext fleet data — the whole point is that only ciphertext is public.
fleet-config.json
fleet-config.csv
*.plaintext.json

# Un-optimised image masters (kept privately at the project root)
image-originals-backup/

# Owner tooling and notes
publish-to-github-repo.command
PUBLISHING.md
HANDOVER.md
launchers/
*.app/

# Local noise
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~
